Annotation: Medical Issues - Complication developed in the hospital

Jargon Term: You were started on three new medications: - Lasix and spironolactone are diuretics which you have been on before. - Midodrine is a medication to keep your blood pressure up.
If you develop fevers>101, severe abdominal pain, nausea, or vomiting, or other symptoms that are concerning to you you should go to the nearest emergency room. .
